HEADWORD: Hydrosulphurous
<hw>Hy`dro*sul"phur*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid obtained
by the reduction of sulphurous acid. See <cref>Hyposulphurous
acid</cref>, under <er>Hyposulphurous</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

